      • newMultiResourcePropertyResolver

        public static org.springframework.core.env.PropertyResolver newMultiResourcePropertyResolver(String builtInResourceLocation,
                                                                             String... customResourceLocations)
                                                                                      throws IOException
        Creates a property resolver that pulls from multiple property resource locations. The first "built-in" location must be successfully loaded, but all other "custom" locations may fail to load.
        Parameters:
        builtInResourceLocation - lowest precedence, required resource location for properties
        customResourceLocations - additional resource locations for properties, in increasing order of precedence
        Returns:
        new property resolver
        Throws:
        IOException - if the built-in resource location could not be loaded
        NullPointerException - if any resource location is null

      • newMultiResourcePropertyResolver

        public static org.springframework.core.env.PropertyResolver newMultiResourcePropertyResolver(boolean allowMissing,
                                                                             String builtInResourceLocation,
                                                                             String... customResourceLocations)
                                                                                      throws IOException
        Creates a property resolver that pulls from multiple property resource locations. The first "built-in" location must be successfully loaded, but all other "custom" locations must load only if {code}allowMissing{code} is false.
        Parameters:
        allowMissing - true to allow custom resource locations to fail to load
        builtInResourceLocation - lowest precedence, required resource location for properties
        customResourceLocations - additional resource locations for properties, in increasing order of precedence
        Returns:
        new property resolver
        Throws:
        IOException - if the built-in resource location could not be loaded, or if {code}allowMissing{code} is false and any custom resource location fails to load
        NullPointerException - if any resource location is null
